SUMMARY:RHA 36th Annual Stream Cleanup @ Scherman Hoffman
DESCRIPTION:On Saturday\, April 18\, 2026\, Raritan Headwaters Association (RHA) will be hosting its 36th Annual Stream Cleanup. 9am-12pm. Thousands of volunteers come together to clean up our rivers and streams\, working to protect essential water supplies across Hunterdon\, Morris\, and Somerset counties. Scherman Hoffman is participating as site location 86. We will break up into small groups and work on picking up trash on the Old Army side of the property and along Hardscrabble Road. Please come dressed for inclement weather with sturdy shoes and multiple layers. Bring a water bottle and sunscreen if necessary. \nMEETING LOCATION: Meet at 9 Hardscrabble Road parking lot. Volunteers for this site will park at the New Jersey Audubon lot. \nMake sure to choose the correct location for your registration! \n\n\n\n\nCOST: FREE \n\n\n\n\n\nInterested in becoming a member? Please click on the following link to learn more or join: Become a Member today! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/rha-36th-annual-stream-cleanup-scherman-hoffman/
LOCATION:New Jersey Audubon’s Scherman Hoffman Wildlife Sanctuary\, 11 Hardscrabble Road\, Bernardsville\, NJ\, 07924\, United States
CATEGORIES:Scherman Hoffman Wildlife Sanctuary,Workshop
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Raritan-Headwaters-35th-Annual-Stream-Clean-Up.jpg
GEO:40.7448693;-74.5523161
